A ROS package for monocular state estimation (using built in webcam on AR Drone 2.0)
http://wiki.ros.org/tum_ardrone

A collection of open slam algorithms (many with open source code)
https://openslam.org/

A opensource monocular slam library (C++)
https://openslam.org/ (RobotVision)

An interesting (ROS) modification of PTAM for use in outdoor enviroments
http://wiki.ros.org/ethzasl_ptam

A nice commentary of how to find position relative to 4 points on a rectangle using opencv:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15727527/how-to-determine-world-coordinates-of-a-camera
